milestones.description: Rahul Dravid and Mohammad Kaif's 132-run partnership is IND's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 127 between Azharuddin and Ajay Sharma

stories.title: Pakistan v India
stories.subTitle: Fourth One-Day International
stories.summary: In front of the biggest contingent of Indian fans on the tour so far, Dravid and Kaif furthered their reputations as men for a crisis.

stories.title: Dravid: 'We set a scorching pace'
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 4th ODI, Lahore
stories.summary: Inzamam-ul-Haq and Rahul Dravid face the press after the fourth ODI at Lahore

stories.title: The thrill of the attack
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 4th ODI, Lahore
stories.summary: One truism that we get to hear a lot these days - ever since Steve Waugh's Australians took the modern game to a pinnacle - is how Test cricket has been improved by the values of one-day cricket, especially as regards aggressive batting and fielding
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by Amit Varma

stories.title: Dravid and Kaif fashion emphatic win
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v India, 4th ODI, Lahore
stories.summary: Nerveless innings by Rahul Dravid and Mohammad Kaif took India to a memorable victory, as they chased down an imposing 294-run target with five overs to spare to level the five-match series at 2-2
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Rahul Bhatia
